<font color="#FF0000">HEY BETTY, ART, ALL OF YOU</font><br>
<tt>Thu Apr 17 23:14:00 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Betty, and to Art, Chet, etc.<br><br>
I know I am guilty of being a pot stirrer.  Whether it is my nature, or my subconscious, I know not.  Critical Thinking has always been my goal.  Debate and interaction my ideals.  I hate mental stagnation and unchallenged thinking, assumptions that prove lethal. Of that I have seen too much.<br><br>
Yes, I stir up emotions.  I can't seem to prevent that.  I do not start with a game plan that says, hmmm, tonight I will fuck with Tom Dier and get him to attach Art.  I just seem to have the knack-curse of reaching into my own psyche and voicing the voices I hear, which more times than not, seems to be the same voice that many of you hear as well.  I can't say I am proud or ashamed, it just is.  <br><br>
Betty, your writing and thinking is a rose to my thorns, please continue.<br><br>
In my 25 years of being a therapist, I truly believe that everyone, every single person I worked with, that I helped or didn't help, rubbed something off on me, left a part of their psyche with me.....perhaps now, I carry too many ghosts of all those souls....but what ever it is, it is me...perhaps that's why I choose the handle of &quot;dr.crazy&quot;<br>
eitherway, I appreciate being accepted as the FNG, and will <br>
do my best, or worst, to continue to provoke, to stir, cause I just don't know how to NOT TO THAT.<br><br>
doc<br>

